14.14 Robustness to PB - Fail-safe N
The Fail-safe N (Rosenthal, 1979) idea is very simple. Given a meta-analysis with a significant result (i.e., \(p \leq \alpha\)). How many null studies (i.e., \(\hat \theta = 0\)) do I need to obtain \(p &gt; \alpha\)?

metafor::fsn(yi, vi, data = dat)
